
Usage:

    mesh-cli [options] <type> <command> <args>

Options:

    -e, --endpoint [url]  API endpoint. (default: http://localhost:8080)
    -k, --key [key]       API Key to be used
    -d, --debug           Turn on debug logging
    -v, --version         output the version number

Types:
   - schema|user|role|group|project|tag|tagfamily|branch|job

Commands:

  Administrative

    configure | config          Configure the CLI
    shell     | sh              Start the interactive shell
    docker    | d               Docker commands
    admin     | a               Administration commands
    push                        Push local changes to the server
    pull   <project>            Pull changes from the server
  
  Management

    list   <type> <project>                 List elements
    add    <type> <id|name> <user|role>
    remove <type> <id|name> <user|role>
    get    <type> <id|name>
    update <type> <id|name>

  Schema 

    validate <filename>                      Validate schema
    link     <id,name> <project> [<branch>]  Link the schema to the project
    unlink   <id,name> <project> [<branch>]  Unlink the schema from the project

  Role
    
    chmod    <id,name> <path>     Update permissions of the role
    roleadd  <group> <role>       Add role to group
    delrole  <group> <role>       Remove role from group

  User

    passwd   <id,name>            Change the password of the user
    key      <id,name>            Generate new API key

  Job

    reset    <id>                 Reset the error state of the job
  
  Other

    help [cmd]                    display help for [cmd]

  Examples:

    $ mesh-cli project schemas demo
    $ mesh-cli user list
    $ mesh-cli user add
